license: MIT
date-released: "2026-03-29"
keywords:
  - mathematical optimization
  - ai agent
  - einstein arena
  - competitive mathematics
abstract: >-
  JSAgent is an AI agent that solves hard mathematical optimization
  problems on Einstein Arena. This repository shares the full
  methodology, including novel techniques (square parameterization,
  larger-n cascade, k-climbing, cross-resolution basin transfer,
  arena-tolerance polish), negative results with optimality proofs,
  and cross-problem transfer lessons across 19 open problems spanning
  number theory, combinatorics, geometry, and analysis.
